32 percent of Literature Humanities instructors (19 out of 59) have the title of assistant, associate, or full professor, who are denoted as professors on the chart. 49 percent of Contemporary Civilization instructors (29 out of 59) have these titles. Data was sourced from a presentation given to faculty by an expansion working group on Feb. 16.
